WEBVTT

00:00.020 --> 00:01.083
<i>Previously on "Suits"...</i>

00:01.084 --> 00:03.044
You made a fool out of Dad
for the last time.

00:03.045 --> 00:03.823
- Harvey...
- Stop it.

00:03.824 --> 00:05.646
You get the hell
out of my father's house.

00:06.587 --> 00:07.919
<i>I am walking out of here</i>

00:07.955 --> 00:09.354
with that thing in my hands,

00:09.389 --> 00:11.089
or I am putting your firm
in the ground.

00:11.124 --> 00:13.825
- Take the painting.
- You told me that painting

00:13.861 --> 00:16.761
<i>was the one happy memory
you had of your mother.</i>

00:16.797 --> 00:18.430
<i>Every application
I filled out today</i>

00:18.465 --> 00:20.065
<i>asked if I was
a convicted felon.</i>

00:20.100 --> 00:22.767
None of these places are gonna
hire me after I check that box.

00:23.003 --> 00:24.747
A legal clinic isn't the only
way to get back.

00:24.771 --> 00:26.171
Are you offering me
a teaching job?

00:26.206 --> 00:27.772
<i>- I am.
- You think this is funny?</i>

00:27.808 --> 00:30.141
Cracks me up that our teacher
was in prison last week.

00:30.177 --> 00:31.776
All you care about
is proving to me

00:31.812 --> 00:33.189
that you should be
managing partner,

00:33.213 --> 00:35.547
when everyone in the world knows
that you shouldn't.

00:35.856 --> 00:38.190
So, if you think I'm gonna let
you be managing partner,

00:38.225 --> 00:40.359
you're out of your
goddamn mind!

00:40.394 --> 00:43.362
One of the students told his
parents that you were in prison.

00:43.397 --> 00:45.697
I tried to explain the situation
to them, but...

00:45.733 --> 00:46.965
I'm sorry, Mike.

00:47.000 --> 00:48.111
They're all leaving,
Donna...

00:48.135 --> 00:49.768
first Jessica and now Mike.

00:49.803 --> 00:51.069
They're family.

00:51.105 --> 00:53.338
You always talk like
we're your only family.

00:53.374 --> 00:55.907
You need to go make things right
with your mother.

00:58.245 --> 01:01.179
<i>[R&B music]</i>

01:01.215 --> 01:08.120
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:11.725 --> 01:13.725
[cup clatters]

01:16.898 --> 01:18.064
Mike, what are
you doing here?

01:18.099 --> 01:19.799
I thought school started
at 7:00.

01:19.834 --> 01:22.335
It does.
I just don't work there anymore.

01:22.370 --> 01:24.103
What?

01:24.138 --> 01:25.972
What happened?

01:26.007 --> 01:28.875
One of the students told their
parents I was a criminal.

01:28.910 --> 01:30.977
They went
to the archdiocese, and...

01:31.012 --> 01:34.013
you know, Father Walker
had no choice.

01:34.048 --> 01:35.948
Why didn't you tell me this
last night?

01:35.984 --> 01:38.251
'Cause I didn't want to step
on your moment.

01:38.619 --> 01:40.786
You were so happy
about Louis' offer.

01:40.821 --> 01:42.221
So what are you gonna do?

01:42.256 --> 01:46.058
I'm gonna take the day
to enjoy my life as a free man.

01:46.093 --> 01:49.861
And then tomorrow...

01:49.897 --> 01:52.698
I'm gonna start all over again.

01:52.733 --> 01:55.667
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

01:55.703 --> 02:01.607
<i>♪ ♪</i>

02:03.675 --> 02:05.641
Hey.

02:05.677 --> 02:07.543
Ray's downstairs
waiting for you.

02:07.579 --> 02:09.078
I didn't call him.

02:09.113 --> 02:10.413
I did.

02:10.448 --> 02:11.992
He's got your black suit
and an overnight bag,

02:12.016 --> 02:13.849
and he's taking you
to the train station.

02:13.885 --> 02:15.284
Donna...

02:15.320 --> 02:16.697
You need to go to your
father's funeral, Harvey.

02:16.721 --> 02:18.287
I can't.
There's too much going on here.

02:18.372 --> 02:20.672
Listen to me--you just
suffered a huge loss,

02:20.707 --> 02:22.683
and you're acting like
it's business as usual.

02:22.684 --> 02:24.818
I'm acting like I've got
a job to do.

02:24.852 --> 02:26.185
Harvey, if you don't
grieve him--

02:26.220 --> 02:28.554
I will grieve my father
in my own way.

02:28.589 --> 02:30.389
No, you won't.

02:30.424 --> 02:33.392
You'll bottle it up,
and you'll try to move on, but--

02:33.427 --> 02:35.394
She's gonna be there, Donna.

02:35.429 --> 02:36.862
I know she is.

02:36.897 --> 02:40.065
But this funeral
isn't about her.

02:40.100 --> 02:42.935
And it's not about you.

02:42.970 --> 02:45.037
It's about your dad...

02:45.072 --> 02:49.575
the man you love more than
anyone in the entire world.

02:49.610 --> 02:50.987
And if you don't
say good-bye to him,

02:51.011 --> 02:55.380
you're gonna regret that
for the rest of your life.

02:55.416 --> 02:58.183
[sighs]

02:58.219 --> 03:01.153
<i>[dramatic rock music]</i>

03:01.188 --> 03:02.487
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:02.905 --> 03:06.306
[knock at door]

03:06.342 --> 03:07.519
Donna, what are you doing here?

03:07.543 --> 03:10.110
The question is,
what are you still doing here?

03:10.145 --> 03:12.079
I made you an 8:00 reservation
to Boston,

03:12.114 --> 03:14.181
which means you should be
halfway there by now.

03:14.216 --> 03:17.684
I missed my flight.

03:17.720 --> 03:20.487
Harvey, you never
miss your flight.

03:20.522 --> 03:22.823
And the last time
you said you did,

03:22.858 --> 03:25.759
you were lying
to me then, too.

03:25.794 --> 03:27.894
- Donna...
- Please tell me

03:27.930 --> 03:29.830
you didn't change your mind
about seeing her.

03:29.865 --> 03:32.099
I didn't.

03:32.134 --> 03:34.167
Then what's the problem?

03:38.510 --> 03:42.011
I haven't seen the woman
in seven years.

03:42.047 --> 03:43.179
The last time I did--

03:43.214 --> 03:46.182
I know what happened
the last time you did.

03:48.219 --> 03:50.653
Listen to me.

03:50.688 --> 03:53.389
Every day you go out
in the world,

03:53.425 --> 03:55.391
and you find a way to win.

03:55.427 --> 03:57.693
It's who you are.
It's what you do.

03:57.729 --> 03:59.095
Donna, this isn't
about winning.

03:59.130 --> 04:01.397
Yes, it is.

04:01.433 --> 04:03.533
But it's not just one person
in this case, it's two,

04:03.568 --> 04:05.868
and right now
you're both losing.

04:09.403 --> 04:11.370
What if I can't do it?

04:11.405 --> 04:13.238
Then don't get on that plane.

04:13.274 --> 04:14.840
But that bag
sitting over there

04:14.875 --> 04:18.177
tells me that you're ready
to forgive her.

04:18.212 --> 04:20.713
And if you are, then that's
all you need to do.

04:22.665 --> 04:26.665
<b><font color="#00FF00">♪ Suits 6x12 ♪</font></b>
<font color="#00FFFF">The Painting</font>
