04:54.218 --> 04:55.984
<i>♪ The greenback boogie ♪</i>

04:56.643 --> 04:58.544
[knock at door]

05:03.260 --> 05:05.026
- Nathan.
- You remember me.

05:05.061 --> 05:07.428
I remember everyone.
What are you doing here?

05:07.464 --> 05:09.041
I'm here because I may not
have been there

05:09.065 --> 05:10.309
when you dropped off
your résumé,

05:10.333 --> 05:13.434
but I still run that clinic.

05:13.470 --> 05:15.603
I'm here to offer you a job.

05:15.639 --> 05:18.406
- I don't understand.
- Hector Suarez.

05:18.441 --> 05:20.975
I'm assuming you remember him,
too, right?

05:21.011 --> 05:22.744
- What about him?
- Well, after you left,

05:22.779 --> 05:24.479
I picked up your file.

05:24.514 --> 05:27.248
Don't tell me--you kept him
in the country.

05:27.284 --> 05:28.917
No, Mike. You did.

05:28.952 --> 05:32.020
I thought, "Maybe this guy
will become a lawyer someday."

05:32.055 --> 05:33.799
And then I read about you
in the paper last year

05:33.823 --> 05:35.089
and found out you never did.

05:35.125 --> 05:37.458
So you knew that I faked
being a lawyer twice,

05:37.494 --> 05:39.327
and you're still here
to offer me a job?

05:39.362 --> 05:43.164
I wouldn't be,
except for this.

05:45.168 --> 05:46.935
You told the truth.

05:46.970 --> 05:48.336
As far as I'm concerned,
that means

05:48.371 --> 05:49.837
you're worth
taking a chance on.

05:49.873 --> 05:51.973
Wow, you really are
a do-gooder.

05:52.008 --> 05:53.508
I'm not here to do good
for you.

05:53.543 --> 05:55.109
I'm here to do good
for my clinic,

05:55.145 --> 05:56.911
because I'm hiring
a partner-level attorney

05:56.947 --> 05:58.357
from one of the top firms
in the city

05:58.381 --> 06:00.682
for the price of the kid
who gets me my coffee.

06:00.717 --> 06:02.028
You have a kid
who gets you coffee?

06:02.052 --> 06:03.451
No, we can't afford that.

06:03.486 --> 06:07.522
But if we could, I'd pay him
what I'm gonna pay you.

06:07.557 --> 06:08.990
So are you in or not?

06:10.860 --> 06:13.194
When do I start?

06:17.200 --> 06:20.902
I don't think I've ever seen
you in a suit before.

06:23.675 --> 06:25.274
Harvey, you made it.

06:25.310 --> 06:27.610
I wouldn't miss it
for the world.

06:35.053 --> 06:37.120
[sighs, chuckles]

06:37.155 --> 06:38.788
Harvey, listen, um--

06:38.823 --> 06:40.690
You don't have to say it.
I know.

06:40.725 --> 06:43.493
She's here.
It's not just that.

06:43.528 --> 06:46.429
She asked if she could say
a few words about Dad.

06:46.464 --> 06:47.697
And what,
you're gonna let her?

06:47.732 --> 06:48.876
- Harvey--
- She is not saying

06:48.900 --> 06:50.833
a single word
as long as I'm here.

06:50.869 --> 06:53.236
Yes, she is,
and if you make a scene

06:53.271 --> 06:54.737
in front of my kids

06:54.773 --> 06:56.806
on the day that we put
our dad into the ground,

06:56.841 --> 06:59.108
I swear to God, I will beat
the shit out of you,

06:59.144 --> 07:03.112
because she's my mother, and
I'm gonna let her say her piece.

07:04.783 --> 07:06.749
Hey.

07:06.785 --> 07:09.552
Harvey...
It's good to see you.

07:09.587 --> 07:12.088
Wish I could say
the same thing, Lily, but...

07:12.123 --> 07:13.823
I'd be lying if I did.

07:14.320 --> 07:17.488
Well, I'm sorry
you feel that way.

07:17.524 --> 07:20.825
And whether you believe it
or not, I loved your father.

07:20.860 --> 07:22.293
And I am sad to see him go.

07:22.328 --> 07:23.694
Yeah, well,
I don't believe it,

07:23.730 --> 07:25.263
and I didn't come here
to see you.

07:25.298 --> 07:26.442
I came here to honor my father,

07:26.466 --> 07:28.332
so get up there,
say what you're gonna say,

07:28.368 --> 07:30.134
and let's get this over with.

07:30.169 --> 07:32.803
[sobs]

07:32.839 --> 07:35.806
<i>[somber music]</i>

07:36.142 --> 07:43.047
<i>♪ ♪</i>

07:49.222 --> 07:50.955
Harvey.

07:50.990 --> 07:52.323
What are you doing here?

07:52.358 --> 07:55.025
I wanted to talk to you.

07:55.061 --> 07:57.862
I can't believe it.
This is wonderful.

07:57.897 --> 07:59.608
I thought maybe you wanted
to get dinner tonight.

07:59.632 --> 08:02.132
There is nothing
I would rather do

08:02.168 --> 08:05.803
than get dinner with you,
but I can't tonight.

08:05.838 --> 08:07.538
I wish
you would have called.

08:07.573 --> 08:10.374
I would have,
but, uh...

08:10.409 --> 08:12.243
You didn't have
my phone number.

08:12.278 --> 08:14.712
No, I didn't.

08:14.747 --> 08:16.747
How about tomorrow night?

08:16.782 --> 08:20.951
I wasn't really planning
on being here two nights.

08:20.987 --> 08:22.953
My firm is in a...

08:22.989 --> 08:24.488
vulnerable spot right now.

08:24.523 --> 08:26.323
Harvey, it's the kids'
art show.

08:26.359 --> 08:31.128
It's once a year.
I can't cancel it.

08:31.163 --> 08:33.097
You know what?
This is silly.

08:33.524 --> 08:35.224
You flew
all the way up here.

08:35.259 --> 08:36.558
No.

08:36.594 --> 08:39.294
We can do it
tomorrow night.

08:41.000 --> 08:47.074
-= www.OpenSubtitles.org =-

08:48.479 --> 08:52.114
Don't tell me.
You took the job.

08:52.150 --> 08:53.949
Actually, until this morning,
I didn't think

08:53.985 --> 08:55.763
there was a chance in hell
I was getting this job.

08:55.787 --> 08:57.464
Sounds to me like you had
a friend at the front desk

08:57.488 --> 08:59.033
who put your résumé
at the top of the pile.

08:59.057 --> 09:01.023
Sounds to me like I owe
that person a beer.

09:01.059 --> 09:02.491
Just so we're clear--
I'm that guy.

09:02.527 --> 09:03.726
I get the picture.

09:03.761 --> 09:06.062
- Welcome to the clinic, Mike.
- Thanks, Oliver.

09:06.097 --> 09:07.930
- I see you met Oliver here.
- I did.

09:07.965 --> 09:09.765
We got along right away.
Good, good.

09:09.801 --> 09:11.333
Well, you're off
to a good start.

09:11.369 --> 09:12.413
I guess the only thing left

09:12.437 --> 09:13.814
is for you to show me
where my desk is.

09:13.838 --> 09:18.507
Right. It's, uh, right inside
that office right there.

09:18.543 --> 09:21.944
I didn't think
I was getting an office.

09:21.979 --> 09:23.512
Look, just because
I'm paying you dick

09:23.548 --> 09:25.426
doesn't mean I'm not gonna
give you the tools for the job.

09:25.450 --> 09:26.894
What exactly is my job?
'Cause as far as I can tell,

09:26.918 --> 09:29.251
I'm the only one here
with an office.

09:29.287 --> 09:30.920
Everybody listen up.

09:31.354 --> 09:32.987
You have a new supervisor
starting today.

09:33.022 --> 09:35.256
His name is Mike Ross.

09:35.291 --> 09:37.058
Mike is from
Pearson Specter Litt,

09:37.093 --> 09:39.527
and he knows more about law
than all of you combined.

09:39.562 --> 09:42.363
So, if Mike tells you to do
something, you do it.

09:42.398 --> 09:44.565
I don't mean to question
the new world order,

09:44.601 --> 09:45.967
but what is his title?

09:46.002 --> 09:49.137
Great question, Marissa.
Um...

09:49.172 --> 09:51.906
senior individual
in charge of you?

09:51.941 --> 09:54.275
Any more queries?
I didn't think so.

09:54.310 --> 09:56.544
All right, back to work.
Let's go.

09:56.773 --> 09:57.839
You really weren't kidding

09:57.874 --> 09:59.352
when you said you were
doing this for you.

09:59.376 --> 10:00.542
No, I wasn't.

10:00.577 --> 10:02.055
I've been trying to get somebody
in this position

10:02.079 --> 10:03.489
for this money
for the last ten years,

10:03.513 --> 10:06.281
and now that I have...

10:06.316 --> 10:07.716
I'm gonna take
full advantage of it.

10:07.751 --> 10:09.462
Then why don't you go back
to wherever your office is

10:09.486 --> 10:10.930
and stay there for the rest
of the year?

10:10.954 --> 10:13.355
'Cause I'll be busy
kicking ass out here.

10:13.390 --> 10:15.757
That's what I like to hear.

10:15.792 --> 10:18.727
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

10:19.062 --> 10:24.132
<i>♪ ♪</i>

10:26.036 --> 10:28.603
Hey, who do you have to know
around here to get a good table?

10:28.638 --> 10:30.638
Jesus Christ.

10:30.674 --> 10:31.973
Do my eyes deceive me,

10:32.008 --> 10:33.908
or do you look
just like my big brother,

10:33.943 --> 10:35.977
only older, fatter,
and douchier?

10:36.012 --> 10:38.513
I appreciate you noticing.
I put in a lot of effort.

10:38.548 --> 10:41.716
Seriously, Harvey,
why are you here?

10:41.751 --> 10:44.952
I thought it was time
to, uh, make my peace with Mom.

10:44.988 --> 10:46.754
Harvey, that's great.

10:46.790 --> 10:50.692
But, uh, a lot has been said
over the years.

10:50.727 --> 10:54.128
You can't just show up
on Mom's door.

10:54.164 --> 10:56.698
Actually, I already did.

10:56.733 --> 10:58.199
What? When?

10:58.234 --> 11:00.168
I went over to the college.

11:00.203 --> 11:02.214
She's having an art opening
tonight for her students,

11:02.238 --> 11:04.972
so we're gonna have dinner
here tomorrow night.

11:05.008 --> 11:07.275
Well, then
I will get you a table.

11:07.931 --> 11:09.564
And what you're going to do

11:09.599 --> 11:12.701
is cancel whatever fancy
bullshit hotel you booked,

11:12.736 --> 11:14.347
and you're going to stay
the night with us.

11:14.371 --> 11:17.138
Marcus, come on, I'm at the
Ambassador Suite at the Ritz.

11:17.174 --> 11:18.640
Don't think of saying no

11:18.675 --> 11:20.453
because I'm going to tell Katie
and the kids that you're here.

11:20.477 --> 11:21.943
You guys offer
room service?

11:21.978 --> 11:22.944
If by "room service,"

11:22.979 --> 11:25.413
you mean string cheese
and Triscuits,

11:25.449 --> 11:27.916
oh, yeah,
we've got room service.

11:27.951 --> 11:30.485
All right,
well, then count me in.

11:31.822 --> 11:34.723
Marissa, right?
Mike.

11:34.758 --> 11:36.458
I know. The new boss.

11:36.493 --> 11:38.727
- [chuckles]
- What?

11:38.762 --> 11:40.628
It's nothing--
it's just where I come from,

11:40.664 --> 11:42.464
the, uh--the bosses
don't bike to work.

11:42.499 --> 11:44.299
I guess this is
no Pearson Specter Litt.

11:44.334 --> 11:47.444
No, it's not, which is
actually why I came here.

11:47.445 --> 11:49.322
I'm glad, because there are
a lot of people here

11:49.346 --> 11:52.648
who could really use your help,
but I'm not one of them.

11:55.052 --> 11:56.585
Aren't you still
a law student?

11:56.620 --> 11:58.265
A law student
who's won every case I've had

11:58.289 --> 11:59.733
since I've been here.
Great, so I guess that means

11:59.757 --> 12:01.189
you have everything
under control

12:01.225 --> 12:02.424
on the Price case, then?

12:02.459 --> 12:03.525
You just got here.

12:03.561 --> 12:04.960
How did you--
I'm a fast reader.

12:04.995 --> 12:06.406
Marissa, I'm not trying
to throw my weight around here

12:06.430 --> 12:07.774
on the first day,
but according to her file,

12:07.798 --> 12:10.065
Miss Price missed
her court date,

12:10.100 --> 12:11.860
which means I need to know
what your plan is.

12:11.908 --> 12:13.774
My plan is
to have Miss Price

12:13.810 --> 12:15.176
explain that she is
a single mother

12:15.211 --> 12:16.856
living in an apartment
with a broken window

12:16.880 --> 12:20.681
and no heat for months, and
they're trying to kick her out.

12:21.083 --> 12:23.250
And if all you're gonna do
is tell the judge

12:23.285 --> 12:25.518
that it's not fair,
you're gonna lose.

12:25.554 --> 12:28.588
You need legal foundation.
I have legal foundation.

12:28.624 --> 12:29.789
Berger v. Chozick--

12:29.825 --> 12:31.691
tenants are permitted to seek
injunctive relief

12:31.727 --> 12:33.693
if vital repair requests
have gone unanswered.

12:33.729 --> 12:35.306
Then I hope you have backup,
'cause the attorneys

12:35.330 --> 12:36.741
representing the other side
have kicked out

12:36.765 --> 12:38.398
300 tenants
in the past six years,

12:38.433 --> 12:39.978
which means
they are not messing around.

12:40.002 --> 12:41.568
I'm not either,
which is why I have

12:41.603 --> 12:43.903
Miss Price coming in
at 3:00 tomorrow.

12:43.939 --> 12:45.516
So is there anything else
I can help you with?

12:45.540 --> 12:47.107
Or maybe
you can spend some time

12:47.142 --> 12:49.576
on some of the other people's
cases around here.

12:49.911 --> 12:54.781
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:59.666 --> 13:01.367
Louis, I need your help.

13:01.402 --> 13:03.380
- Of course. What is it?
- Teddy Doyle just called.

13:03.404 --> 13:04.570
He has an emergency.

13:04.605 --> 13:05.904
So you mean Harvey
needs my help.

13:05.940 --> 13:06.872
- Louis--
- Donna, give me

13:06.907 --> 13:08.741
one good reason
why I should help him.

13:08.776 --> 13:10.142
You're not helping
Harvey, Louis.

13:10.177 --> 13:12.222
You're helping the firm.
Teddy is a client of all of us.

13:12.246 --> 13:14.913
No, Harvey made it clear
that there is no us.

13:14.949 --> 13:16.827
Louis, Harvey's going
through something right now.

13:16.851 --> 13:18.350
His outburst
wasn't about you.

13:18.386 --> 13:20.419
You can believe
whatever you want,

13:20.454 --> 13:23.389
but Harvey lashed out at me,
and now he's not even man enough

13:23.424 --> 13:25.629
to come to me to ask me
for help himself?

13:25.729 --> 13:27.274
Why should I even lift a finger
to help him?

13:27.298 --> 13:30.499
Because he went to go make
things right with his mother.

13:30.534 --> 13:33.769
And he did it because of how he
felt after he lashed out at you.

13:33.804 --> 13:37.473
Otherwise, he'd be taking care
of Teddy himself.

13:37.508 --> 13:40.709
So you want
to help him or not?

13:41.039 --> 13:43.407
What do you need me to do?

13:47.112 --> 13:49.479
Mike?
What's going on?

13:49.515 --> 13:51.059
Rachel. I thought you weren't
getting home till 8:00.

13:51.083 --> 13:53.283
- It's 8:30.
- I guess I lost track of time.

13:53.318 --> 13:55.585
I have just been buried
in this paperwork.

13:55.621 --> 13:59.489
Yeah, I can see that.
Are we being audited?

13:59.525 --> 14:00.991
I got a job.

14:01.026 --> 14:02.537
And I would have called you
right away,

14:02.561 --> 14:04.773
but I've been swamped from the
minute I walked into the clinic.

14:04.797 --> 14:06.897
You got a job
at a legal clinic?

14:06.932 --> 14:09.366
Mike, that's amazing.
Yeah, it is.

14:09.401 --> 14:12.102
- Um...
- Yes, they know about me.

14:12.137 --> 14:14.738
In fact, it's the reason
I got hired.

14:14.773 --> 14:17.174
Let me guess--they were
smart enough to appreciate

14:17.209 --> 14:18.809
they can get someone
with your experience

14:18.844 --> 14:20.677
for ten cents on the dollar.

14:21.310 --> 14:22.310
You got it.

14:22.345 --> 14:26.313
$35,000 a year
to be exact.

14:26.349 --> 14:28.416
Mm!
Which means...

14:28.451 --> 14:30.918
we should probably start
packing up the place now,

14:30.953 --> 14:34.922
'cause we definitely cannot
afford to live here anymore.

14:34.957 --> 14:38.225
I would live
in a shoebox with you

14:38.261 --> 14:39.660
if it meant you were happy.

14:39.695 --> 14:42.029
Aw, I think you meant that you
would live in a shoebox

14:42.065 --> 14:45.066
as long as the Thai place
still delivered.

14:45.101 --> 14:47.968
- And the sushi place.
- Of course.

14:52.108 --> 14:54.375
- Want one?
- You kidding me?

14:54.410 --> 14:57.111
After reading "Pinkalicious"
for the seventh time,

14:57.146 --> 14:58.545
I need a six-pack.

14:58.581 --> 14:59.813
[chuckles]

14:59.849 --> 15:02.816
[bottle cap clatters]

15:02.852 --> 15:04.118
[sighs]

15:04.153 --> 15:07.588
[sighs] It was nice
putting them to bed.

15:07.623 --> 15:09.556
Oh, yeah,
let's hear you say that

15:09.592 --> 15:12.062
after doing it
365 days a year.

15:12.162 --> 15:14.696
I thought Katie put them
to bed most nights.

15:14.731 --> 15:17.565
Yeah.
I was saying it for her.

15:17.601 --> 15:19.034
[chuckles]

15:19.069 --> 15:21.670
Thanks for making me
stay over, Marcus.

15:22.005 --> 15:24.572
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:24.607 --> 15:27.141
Well, maybe after
tomorrow night,

15:27.177 --> 15:29.077
you can do it more often.

15:29.112 --> 15:31.713
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:31.748 --> 15:33.715
Maybe.

15:33.750 --> 15:36.684
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:36.720 --> 15:40.021
Thank you all for coming.

15:40.056 --> 15:41.622
I'm Lily.

15:41.658 --> 15:44.959
I was married to Gordon
for almost 30 years.

15:44.995 --> 15:48.262
We didn't make it the whole 30,
and for a long time,

15:48.298 --> 15:51.699
I considered myself a failure
because of that.

15:51.735 --> 15:54.702
But Gordon didn't.

15:54.738 --> 15:56.437
A few years
after our divorce,

15:56.473 --> 16:00.208
I wanted to apologize
for things not working out.

16:02.212 --> 16:04.946
He just smiled and said,

16:04.981 --> 16:07.548
"Lily, what the hell
are you talking about?

16:07.584 --> 16:09.484
"We achieved something together

16:09.519 --> 16:12.954
that neither one of us
could have done on our own."

16:14.657 --> 16:17.258
Our sons...

16:17.293 --> 16:19.494
Harvey and Marcus.

16:19.529 --> 16:21.662
When Gordon was on the road,
he would call home...

16:21.698 --> 16:25.133
[chuckles] Six times a day
to check on them.

16:25.168 --> 16:27.268
Did they eat enough dinner?

16:27.303 --> 16:30.271
Had they done homework?

16:30.306 --> 16:34.275
How many points
did Marcus score?

16:34.310 --> 16:37.678
Did Harvey get his tux
for the prom?

16:37.714 --> 16:40.615
Gordon was proud
of a lot of things in his life,

16:40.650 --> 16:43.051
but none of it compared

16:43.086 --> 16:45.253
to how proud he was of them.

16:45.288 --> 16:47.221
<i>[somber music]</i>

16:48.259 --> 16:50.726
They were his everything.

16:50.761 --> 16:53.062
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:53.097 --> 16:57.099
No matter where he is...
[sniffles]

16:57.134 --> 16:59.968
I know he is watching
over them right now.

17:00.004 --> 17:06.909
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:19.013 --> 17:21.146
- What are you doing here?
- Doing my job.

17:21.183 --> 17:23.116
- This is my case, not yours.
- No, Marissa.

17:23.151 --> 17:24.818
It's our case.
We're on the same side.

17:24.853 --> 17:27.420
And if you'd just listen to me,
you might learn something.

17:27.455 --> 17:28.500
- Like what?
- Like the ways

17:28.523 --> 17:29.990
experienced attorneys
can trick you.

17:30.025 --> 17:31.825
I'm not gonna
get tricked, so...

17:31.860 --> 17:33.838
if you don't mind,
I'd like to meet with my client.

17:33.862 --> 17:35.328
I've already met with her.

17:35.364 --> 17:37.264
You met her without me?

17:37.299 --> 17:38.932
When did you do this?
Half hour ago.

17:38.967 --> 17:40.445
You said 3:00,
so I called her in at 2:30

17:40.469 --> 17:42.580
because I knew you wouldn't
give me the chance to meet her,

17:42.604 --> 17:43.970
just like I know
the other side

17:44.006 --> 17:45.805
is gonna approach her
when you're not there.

17:45.841 --> 17:47.908
- They can't do that.
- Why? Because it's unfair?

17:47.943 --> 17:49.888
- Because it's illegal.
- Only if she pursues them,

17:49.912 --> 17:51.890
which she'll never do
because they're gonna find out

17:51.914 --> 17:53.758
whatever her weak spots are,
and then they're gonna offer her

17:53.782 --> 17:55.815
exactly the amount
she needs to get by,

17:55.851 --> 17:57.617
and then
she's gonna take it.

17:57.653 --> 17:59.253
If she does that,
she'll end up homeless.

17:59.288 --> 18:02.355
Which is why we need to be
prepared for it to happen.

18:02.391 --> 18:05.125
Now, do you want to work on this
thing together or not?

18:05.160 --> 18:08.094
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

18:08.430 --> 18:14.200
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:14.236 --> 18:15.535
I'm sorry I didn't tell you

18:15.570 --> 18:18.905
that she was gonna speak
before you got here.

18:18.940 --> 18:21.107
I just didn't have it in me
to have it out with you.

18:21.142 --> 18:22.508
It's okay, Marcus.

18:25.180 --> 18:27.647
She got to you, didn't she?

18:27.682 --> 18:29.716
I'm sad about Dad.

18:29.751 --> 18:32.585
And, yeah, she pulled
on that string,

18:32.621 --> 18:36.389
but one speech
doesn't make up for everything.

18:36.424 --> 18:38.691
Maybe it doesn't.

18:38.727 --> 18:42.295
But you have
to start somewhere.

18:42.330 --> 18:43.630
Yeah.

18:43.665 --> 18:45.899
Well...

18:45.934 --> 18:47.267
I'm gonna head back home.

18:47.302 --> 18:50.970
Oh, come on, Harvey,
come to the house for the wake.

18:51.006 --> 18:53.072
I got a few things
I got to take care of at work.

18:53.108 --> 18:56.075
Oh, come on, Harvey, you're
not leaving because of work.

18:56.411 --> 19:00.947
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:00.982 --> 19:03.816
It's time to let things go.

19:07.391 --> 19:10.192
I complained about the heat
not working a million times.

19:10.227 --> 19:11.738
Landlord always says
he's gonna fix it,

19:11.762 --> 19:13.062
and then nothing happens.

19:13.097 --> 19:15.364
We couldn't afford to move,
so I was just making do,

19:15.399 --> 19:18.867
but then my little guy--
he got asthma.

19:19.282 --> 19:23.718
The doctor said that we need
to keep all of the windows shut,

19:23.753 --> 19:25.019
keep out the pollution,

19:25.054 --> 19:27.321
but the window
in the living room--

19:27.357 --> 19:29.523
it's been broken
for seven months.

19:29.559 --> 19:31.392
My son is only
three years old.

19:31.427 --> 19:34.128
The sound of him wheezing
at night...

19:34.163 --> 19:36.864
not knowing if he's gonna
wake up in the morning...

19:36.899 --> 19:40.201
So I thought, "Since that
slumlord only cares about money,

19:40.236 --> 19:41.502
"I'm not gonna pay rent

19:41.537 --> 19:43.704
until he fixes the window
and turns on the heat."

19:43.740 --> 19:45.706
I'm so sorry, Sofia.

19:45.742 --> 19:48.642
That sounds terrible.
It is.

19:48.678 --> 19:51.312
And no one should have
to live like that.

19:51.575 --> 19:54.643
But by violating your lease,
he has grounds to evict you,

19:54.678 --> 19:56.345
which is why you have
to give him a check

19:56.380 --> 19:58.714
for the money you owe him
while this case moves forward.

19:58.749 --> 20:00.449
I-I can't do that.

20:00.484 --> 20:02.050
You don't have
the money anymore.

20:02.086 --> 20:04.653
I had to buy blankets,
space heaters.

20:04.688 --> 20:07.656
There were a couple of nights
that AJ's breathing was so bad,

20:07.691 --> 20:09.992
we had to go to a motel
down the street.

20:10.027 --> 20:11.393
Don't worry, Sofia.

20:11.428 --> 20:13.195
Not only are we gonna get
your window fixed,

20:13.230 --> 20:16.498
but I promise you, you'll get
to keep your home, too.

20:16.533 --> 20:19.668
[chuckles]
Thank you.

20:20.003 --> 20:23.571
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:25.913 --> 20:28.047
Are you crazy?

20:28.083 --> 20:29.349
What are you talking about?

20:29.384 --> 20:31.028
You just told her you were
gonna fix her problem.

20:31.052 --> 20:32.552
Because I'm going
to fix her problem.

20:32.587 --> 20:34.098
That's not the point.
Even if you think

20:34.122 --> 20:35.299
you can make everything better,

20:35.323 --> 20:38.625
you don't guarantee that
to a client.

20:38.856 --> 20:40.155
You know what?

20:40.191 --> 20:42.424
Maybe you don't care
about these people, but I do.

20:42.459 --> 20:43.492
Oh, God.

20:43.527 --> 20:44.905
And I'm willing to fight
to make sure

20:44.929 --> 20:46.473
they stay in their home, and
I'm not afraid to tell her that.

20:46.497 --> 20:48.730
This is not about caring.

20:48.766 --> 20:51.066
There's a real world out there,
and like I told you,

20:51.101 --> 20:52.512
there's an experienced lawyer
on the other side

20:52.536 --> 20:54.303
looking to exploit
our mistakes.

20:54.338 --> 20:55.816
If you over-promise
and under-deliver,

20:55.840 --> 20:57.384
you're just making them
that much more vulnerable

20:57.408 --> 20:58.807
to a shitty offer.

20:58.843 --> 21:00.620
Is that what they taught you
in Corporate Lowballing 101?

21:00.644 --> 21:01.844
Excuse me?

21:01.879 --> 21:03.256
You don't give a shit
about these people,

21:03.280 --> 21:05.047
and Nathan
and everyone else here

21:05.082 --> 21:06.815
might be buying your bullshit,

21:06.851 --> 21:10.385
but I know
why you're really here.

21:10.421 --> 21:13.155
I get it.
You checked up on me.

21:13.190 --> 21:14.656
I didn't need
to check up on you.

21:14.692 --> 21:16.425
I've heard your story
a thousand times.

21:16.460 --> 21:18.460
You couldn't hack it
at your corporate law firm,

21:18.495 --> 21:20.440
so you're slumming it here
until you can figure out

21:20.464 --> 21:22.397
a way to jump
back into your cushy,

21:22.433 --> 21:26.168
stick-it-to-the-working-man job.

21:26.503 --> 21:27.536
[sighs]

21:27.571 --> 21:29.571
I see that I'm right.

21:29.606 --> 21:32.440
So keep your wisdom
to yourself,

21:32.476 --> 21:35.043
because I'm actually here
to help people,

21:35.078 --> 21:39.080
not just remind them what
a cruel world it is out there.

21:39.116 --> 21:42.050
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

21:42.385 --> 21:43.685
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:43.720 --> 21:45.320
[telephone ringing]

21:45.355 --> 21:48.890
- Harvey Specter's office.
<i>- Donna, it's me.</i>

21:48.925 --> 21:51.192
Harvey. Hey.
Are you almost here?

21:51.228 --> 21:53.027
<i>Because your 6:00</i>
<i>is in the conference room.</i>

21:53.063 --> 21:55.129
I'm not back
in New York yet.

21:55.165 --> 21:57.599
<i>You were right, Donna.</i>
About what?

21:57.634 --> 21:59.501
If I'd missed his funeral,

21:59.536 --> 22:02.203
I never would be able
to forgive myself.

22:02.439 --> 22:04.872
[sighs]

22:04.908 --> 22:07.442
Good luck making up
with your mom.

22:07.477 --> 22:09.143
How did you know?

22:09.179 --> 22:10.845
<i>Because you've never missed</i>
<i>a flight</i>

22:10.880 --> 22:11.979
in your entire life.

22:12.015 --> 22:13.715
And the only reason
you'd stay longer

22:13.750 --> 22:17.118
is if things were going better
than you thought they would.

22:18.619 --> 22:19.863
Thanks, Donna.

22:19.864 --> 22:21.531
<i>I don't need</i>
<i>your thanks, Harvey.</i>

22:21.566 --> 22:24.133
I'm just really happy
you're there.

22:24.169 --> 22:27.103
<i>[melancholy music]</i>

22:27.138 --> 22:32.675
<i>♪ ♪</i>

22:32.710 --> 22:34.210
I know
what you're thinking.

22:34.245 --> 22:36.112
How could she not know?

22:36.147 --> 22:38.080
- I checked the box.
- You did.

22:38.116 --> 22:40.650
But I was the one who brought
the application to Nathan,

22:40.685 --> 22:42.251
and he told me
not to tell anyone.

22:42.287 --> 22:43.519
Why not?

22:43.555 --> 22:45.221
Because he didn't want them
to judge you.

22:45.256 --> 22:47.623
I would have thought
everyone knew anyway.

22:47.659 --> 22:49.559
Why would you think that?

22:49.594 --> 22:51.071
Because it was all over
"The Journal."

22:51.095 --> 22:53.129
People here don't read
"The Journal."

22:53.164 --> 22:55.264
We read
"The Huffington Post."

22:55.300 --> 22:56.899
[chuckles]

22:56.935 --> 22:58.801
So what Marissa thinks
is what they all think?

22:58.836 --> 23:00.636
I don't know,
but for what it's worth,

23:00.672 --> 23:01.815
I wouldn't have said anything

23:01.839 --> 23:04.473
whether Nathan told me
to or not.

23:04.509 --> 23:06.642
It's not my story to tell.

23:06.678 --> 23:08.311
Thank you, Oliver.

23:08.346 --> 23:09.745
Yeah.

23:09.781 --> 23:16.719
<i>♪ ♪</i>

23:45.285 --> 23:48.552
You made
your strawberry pie.

23:48.588 --> 23:50.621
It was his favorite.

23:50.657 --> 23:53.057
Maybe you forgot
it was mine, too.

23:53.092 --> 23:55.092
I didn't forget.

23:57.530 --> 23:59.897
It was a nice speech.

23:59.933 --> 24:01.866
Thank you, Harvey.

24:04.904 --> 24:07.438
Harvey...

24:07.473 --> 24:08.739
when my parents died,

24:08.775 --> 24:12.276
I felt like I was completely
alone in the world.

24:12.312 --> 24:14.712
I don't want you
to feel that way.

24:14.747 --> 24:17.848
I want you to know
that whether you want me

24:17.884 --> 24:20.284
in your life or not,

24:20.320 --> 24:23.321
you still have a mother
that loves you

24:23.356 --> 24:26.057
and will always
be there for you.

24:28.701 --> 24:30.634
I know that.

24:33.405 --> 24:37.241
Harvey, I'm--
I'm sorry for your loss.

24:39.345 --> 24:40.611
Are you kidding me?

24:40.646 --> 24:43.046
You brought him here?
Harvey--

24:43.082 --> 24:45.082
I said, you have the nerve
to bring him here?

24:45.117 --> 24:46.661
- He's my partner.
- Is that what you call

24:46.685 --> 24:48.296
every guy you slept with
while you were with Dad?

24:48.320 --> 24:51.588
Don't speak to me like that.
Bobby and I are still together.

24:51.624 --> 24:53.690
- You think I give a shit?
- You should...

24:53.726 --> 24:55.492
because it shows what kind
of man I am.

24:55.528 --> 24:57.794
You're a piece of shit.
You have no right being here

24:57.830 --> 24:59.663
the day we put my father
in the ground.

24:59.698 --> 25:02.165
Harvey, please.
We were just about--

25:02.201 --> 25:04.034
Yeah, I don't care
what we were about to do.

25:04.069 --> 25:05.802
You spit in Dad's face
by bringing him here.

25:05.838 --> 25:06.803
I-it's okay.

25:06.839 --> 25:07.871
Lily, I'll go.

25:07.907 --> 25:09.439
I don't care
whether you stay or not.

25:09.475 --> 25:12.342
No, well, I do,
and he is staying,

25:12.378 --> 25:14.278
because you may not
want to hear this,

25:14.313 --> 25:17.080
but your father accepted him
a long time ago.

25:17.116 --> 25:18.894
You know what? You want
to take his place, Bobby,

25:18.918 --> 25:20.317
why don't you go right ahead?

25:20.352 --> 25:22.397
Maybe one day you'll even walk
in on her with another guy,

25:22.421 --> 25:24.488
and you'll know exactly
what my father felt.

25:24.523 --> 25:25.600
The only difference will be

25:25.624 --> 25:27.624
at least then...

25:27.660 --> 25:30.561
I won't be asked to keep
the goddamn secret.

25:30.596 --> 25:33.530
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

25:33.566 --> 25:38.702
<i>♪ ♪</i>

25:42.366 --> 25:44.103
So, what's good here?

25:44.104 --> 25:46.871
Actually, everything's
good here.

25:46.907 --> 25:48.806
You eat here a lot?

25:48.842 --> 25:50.441
Of course I do.

25:55.916 --> 25:59.584
[chuckles]
This...

25:59.619 --> 26:01.786
This feels strange,
doesn't it?

26:01.821 --> 26:03.688
Yeah, a little bit.

26:03.723 --> 26:06.758
So, where do we start?

26:10.330 --> 26:12.297
I guess we start
with me telling you

26:12.332 --> 26:16.134
that I'm ready
to forgive you.

26:16.169 --> 26:19.003
[sighs]
Why now?

26:19.039 --> 26:23.574
Someone very special to me
convinced me that I needed to.

26:23.610 --> 26:26.778
Whoever it is...

26:26.813 --> 26:29.480
I'm glad she did.

26:29.516 --> 26:30.815
That's good.

26:30.850 --> 26:33.251
I want you to know...

26:33.286 --> 26:36.621
that I forgive you, too.

26:36.656 --> 26:38.256
Forgive me?
For what?

26:38.291 --> 26:39.590
For the last time I saw you

26:39.626 --> 26:41.137
and for you being gone
all those years.

26:41.161 --> 26:42.493
I had my reasons
to be gone.

26:42.529 --> 26:44.696
Yes, you did,
when you were younger,

26:44.731 --> 26:46.130
but you're not
a child anymore,

26:46.166 --> 26:48.333
and you haven't been
for a long time.

26:48.368 --> 26:49.400
I can't believe you.

26:49.436 --> 26:50.969
You're turning this
around on me?

26:51.004 --> 26:54.472
I'm not turning it
around, Harvey.

26:54.507 --> 26:57.642
You have no idea what it's like
to have a child

26:57.677 --> 26:59.877
who acts
like you don't even exist.

26:59.913 --> 27:01.713
You don't know what it's like
to have a mother

27:01.748 --> 27:04.482
who asks you to lie
to his own father for her.

27:04.517 --> 27:07.185
Harvey, I never
should have done that,

27:07.220 --> 27:08.720
and I have been trying
to tell you

27:08.755 --> 27:11.055
I am sorry about it
for 20 years,

27:11.091 --> 27:13.291
but until yesterday,
you made it clear to me

27:13.326 --> 27:16.160
that you had no interest
in whether I lived or died.

27:16.196 --> 27:18.763
- Because I didn't.
- Well, can't you understand

27:18.798 --> 27:21.332
how that could devastate
a person?

27:21.368 --> 27:24.002
I can understand
how this was just a mistake,

27:24.037 --> 27:26.504
because you are the same
selfish, self-centered,

27:26.539 --> 27:28.272
disloyal woman
you always were.

27:28.308 --> 27:29.874
And you are the same
self-absorbed,

27:29.909 --> 27:31.976
childish man
you always were.

27:32.012 --> 27:33.611
Well, whose fault is that?

27:33.646 --> 27:35.613
Oh. There you go. Leave.

27:35.648 --> 27:37.715
That's what you do best.
What'd you just say to me?

27:37.751 --> 27:39.328
I said take a look
in the mirror, Harvey,

27:39.352 --> 27:41.819
because I may have neglected
my family in the past,

27:41.855 --> 27:45.456
but you've been doing it
for as long as I can remember.

27:45.492 --> 27:48.459
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

27:48.495 --> 27:55.400
<i>♪ ♪</i>

28:02.653 --> 28:04.988
So what am I supposed to tell
the kids in the morning?

28:05.023 --> 28:07.657
You tell them I've got
business back in New York.

28:08.121 --> 28:09.720
You want me to lie for you?

28:09.756 --> 28:11.222
Marcus,
she had the nerve

28:11.257 --> 28:13.691
to say that I owed her
an apology.

28:13.726 --> 28:15.226
[knock at door]

28:15.261 --> 28:17.339
If that's her, you tell her
I've got nothing more to say.

28:17.363 --> 28:18.396
You know what, Harvey?

28:18.431 --> 28:19.630
You can tell her yourself,

28:19.666 --> 28:21.799
because I'm doing being
in the middle of you two.

28:25.071 --> 28:26.370
Bobby.
Where is he?

28:26.406 --> 28:28.573
- Hey, now's not the time.
- You son of a bitch.

28:28.608 --> 28:30.185
You think you can just walk
into our lives

28:30.209 --> 28:31.909
and--and rip open
old wounds?

28:31.945 --> 28:33.311
Your lives?
You better get the hell

28:33.346 --> 28:35.680
out of my face before I do
something that you'll regret.

28:35.715 --> 28:37.114
You already did something
I regret

28:37.150 --> 28:38.790
by talking to your mother
the way you did.

28:38.826 --> 28:41.293
That woman gave up the right
to be called my mother

28:41.328 --> 28:43.562
when she got together with you
behind my father's back.

28:43.597 --> 28:45.730
Well, maybe you don't consider
her to be your mother,

28:45.766 --> 28:48.033
but she's my wife,
and if anyone else spoke to her

28:48.068 --> 28:49.913
the way you did, they'd be
on the floor right now.

28:49.937 --> 28:51.114
You want to take
a swing at me?

28:51.138 --> 28:52.282
- Harvey, Harvey--
- No, no, no.

28:52.306 --> 28:53.638
Let him get it
out of his system,

28:53.674 --> 28:57.042
'cause I know I want
to get it out of mine.

28:57.077 --> 29:00.045
I didn't come here
to fight, Harvey.

29:00.080 --> 29:01.179
I came here to tell you

29:01.215 --> 29:03.181
I've never seen your mother
more excited

29:03.217 --> 29:06.117
than when she was heading out
to have dinner with you.

29:06.347 --> 29:09.081
She was finally gonna get
to reconnect with her son.

29:09.116 --> 29:11.094
And then you pulled the rug out
from underneath her.

29:11.118 --> 29:12.751
You took that excitement away.

29:12.787 --> 29:14.720
So, when you leave this time,
just stay gone,

29:14.755 --> 29:16.989
because the truth is,

29:17.024 --> 29:19.425
this family works better
without you.

29:19.460 --> 29:25.831
<i>♪ ♪</i>

29:27.629 --> 29:28.906
Rachel, I need you
to help me with something,

29:28.930 --> 29:30.296
and I need it quickly.
What is it?

29:30.332 --> 29:31.864
Teddy Doyle needs to access

29:31.900 --> 29:33.444
the proceeds from the sale
of his company

29:33.468 --> 29:35.234
that were put in trust
to avoid taxes,

29:35.270 --> 29:37.670
and he needs to do it
without triggering those taxes.

29:37.706 --> 29:39.939
Louis, are you kidding?
This isn't Dubai.

29:39.974 --> 29:41.152
He's not gonna be able
to do that.

29:41.176 --> 29:45.411
I know that, but I need him
to be able to anyway.

29:45.730 --> 29:46.862
Give me the file.

29:46.897 --> 29:48.564
I'll figure something out.
Thanks.

29:48.599 --> 29:51.133
I'm proud of you, Louis.

29:51.168 --> 29:52.267
For what?

29:52.303 --> 29:53.902
Teddy Doyle is
Harvey's client.

29:53.938 --> 29:55.537
And I heard about your thing.

29:55.573 --> 29:59.008
So this must mean
that you forgave him.

29:59.043 --> 30:01.010
I did.

30:01.045 --> 30:03.612
Bring that to me as soon
as you have something.

30:03.648 --> 30:09.051
<i>♪ ♪</i>

30:09.284 --> 30:11.384
Hey, Mike, I got a question
about the Haberman case.

30:11.420 --> 30:13.086
He lost his job.
They're taking his car.

30:13.121 --> 30:14.087
I'm trying--

30:14.122 --> 30:15.522
You need
a reaffirmation agreement.

30:15.557 --> 30:16.990
Can I help you in a minute?
Yeah.

30:17.025 --> 30:18.425
Great.

30:21.363 --> 30:23.964
Hey, everyone, can you listen
up for a sec?

30:25.783 --> 30:28.651
Marissa...

30:28.686 --> 30:30.319
this won't take long.

30:32.256 --> 30:33.734
When Nathan introduced me,
he told you

30:33.758 --> 30:36.058
that I used to work
at Pearson Specter Litt.

30:36.093 --> 30:39.928
What he didn't tell you is
why I don't work there anymore.

30:39.964 --> 30:41.330
And the reason isn't

30:41.365 --> 30:44.600
that I couldn't hack it
as a corporate lawyer.

30:44.635 --> 30:47.002
It's because I wasn't
a lawyer at all.

30:47.038 --> 30:49.171
<i>♪ ♪</i>

30:49.206 --> 30:51.307
Here, read that.

30:51.342 --> 30:53.809
<i>♪ ♪</i>

30:54.071 --> 30:55.938
That is my story.

30:55.973 --> 30:58.007
That's what I did.

30:58.042 --> 31:02.177
Every word of these articles
is true.

31:02.213 --> 31:06.348
I never should have been
at Pearson Specter.

31:06.384 --> 31:08.417
But not being a lawyer
isn't the only reason

31:08.452 --> 31:10.185
I didn't belong there.

31:10.221 --> 31:11.654
You see, the whole reason

31:11.689 --> 31:13.923
that I wanted to be a lawyer
in the first place

31:13.958 --> 31:15.791
was so that I could help
the kind of people

31:15.826 --> 31:18.360
that come into this clinic
every single day.

31:18.396 --> 31:20.062
Now, I thought
you all knew this,

31:20.097 --> 31:22.131
but it's clear to me now
that you don't.

31:22.166 --> 31:25.901
Nathan wanted to protect me,

31:25.937 --> 31:28.270
but...

31:28.306 --> 31:30.906
I'd rather have you respect me.

31:31.275 --> 31:33.208
If any of you have
any questions at all,

31:33.243 --> 31:34.843
please come talk to me
about it.

31:34.878 --> 31:37.379
If not, let's get back to work.

31:37.414 --> 31:41.116
<i>♪ ♪</i>

31:41.260 --> 31:44.228
Mike.

31:44.263 --> 31:47.998
You didn't have to do that.

31:48.034 --> 31:50.000
Yeah, I did.

31:50.036 --> 31:56.407
<i>♪ ♪</i>

31:56.643 --> 31:58.876
Hey.

31:58.912 --> 32:00.178
You're still here.

32:00.213 --> 32:03.214
My flight isn't
for another two hours.

32:03.250 --> 32:05.483
I wasn't gonna let that asshole
drive me away.

32:05.518 --> 32:08.753
Listen, Harvey, about what
Bobby said last night--

32:08.788 --> 32:10.499
You don't need to make excuses
for him, Marcus.

32:10.523 --> 32:12.123
Oh, I'm not making excuses.

32:12.158 --> 32:13.758
I'm telling you
he had every right

32:13.793 --> 32:15.026
to say what he said to you.

32:15.061 --> 32:16.739
I don't believe this.
You're on his side now?

32:16.763 --> 32:18.563
The only side I'm on
is my family's--

32:18.598 --> 32:20.431
the family that you've never
been a part of.

32:20.433 --> 32:22.466
- Marcus, come on.
- Do you know what it's like

32:22.501 --> 32:24.701
to tell a five-year-old
why Grandma

32:24.737 --> 32:27.037
and Uncle Harvey can't be
in the same room together?

32:27.072 --> 32:30.741
Because that's the position
you put me in year after year.

32:30.776 --> 32:33.076
There's a whole life
going on here

32:33.112 --> 32:35.212
that you're not even
a part of.

32:35.247 --> 32:36.980
You think I don't know
what I've missed?

32:37.016 --> 32:39.049
I'm not just talking
about birthdays, Harvey.

32:45.443 --> 32:48.511
I got sick again,
couple years ago.

32:48.546 --> 32:50.880
What?

32:50.915 --> 32:52.982
Why didn't you tell me?
Why would I?

32:53.017 --> 32:55.317
So that we could have this
at the same time?

32:55.353 --> 32:56.852
- Marcus--
- No, listen to me.

32:56.888 --> 33:01.190
You know who helped out when
Katie was taking me to chemo?

33:01.225 --> 33:04.026
Mom made dinner every night.

33:04.061 --> 33:07.096
Bobby took my kids
to school every day,

33:07.131 --> 33:08.497
which means...

33:08.533 --> 33:12.134
while they might be
monsters to you,

33:12.170 --> 33:16.739
to my kids,
they're Grandma and Grandpa.

33:17.196 --> 33:20.431
And you might not like that shit
coming from Bobby,

33:20.466 --> 33:22.967
but it's the truth, Harvey...

33:23.002 --> 33:24.969
whether you want
to hear it or not.

33:25.004 --> 33:28.572
<i>♪ ♪</i>

33:32.013 --> 33:34.247
Do you have a minute?

33:34.282 --> 33:36.249
Of course.

33:36.284 --> 33:38.151
I'm sorry
that I misjudged you.

33:38.186 --> 33:40.486
It's okay.

33:40.522 --> 33:42.021
Like I said,
we're on the same team.

33:42.056 --> 33:44.957
We are, and I also
should not have promised Sofia

33:44.993 --> 33:46.092
that we would win.

33:46.127 --> 33:47.705
But I told you
that I wouldn't stop looking

33:47.729 --> 33:49.162
for a way to keep her
in her home,

33:49.197 --> 33:50.463
and I think I found one.

33:50.498 --> 33:51.876
Marissa, it doesn't matter
what kind

33:51.900 --> 33:53.199
of legal basis you've got.

33:53.234 --> 33:55.001
If she can't pay her rent
in the meantime--

33:55.036 --> 33:57.036
That's what I'm talking
about--Troy v. Suffolk.

33:57.071 --> 33:59.183
As long as we can prove that she
tried to tell the landlord

33:59.207 --> 34:01.107
about the heat--
Yeah, but we can't prove it.

34:01.142 --> 34:02.742
She doesn't have it in writing.

34:02.777 --> 34:04.177
We can if we use
the phone records.

34:04.212 --> 34:05.945
Phone records aren't proof
of a complaint.

34:05.980 --> 34:08.447
No, but the only people
who call their landlord

34:08.483 --> 34:09.726
three times a week
for two months

34:09.751 --> 34:12.251
are people who have a problem
that needs fixing.

34:16.172 --> 34:17.472
Then we enter
the motel receipts

34:17.507 --> 34:18.985
and the receipts
for the space heaters

34:19.009 --> 34:20.809
as substitution for rent paid.

34:20.844 --> 34:22.543
And not only
can he not evict her,

34:22.579 --> 34:25.047
she doesn't have to pay
back rent.

34:25.081 --> 34:26.681
We just need
to convince the court

34:26.717 --> 34:28.250
to accept these phone records.

34:28.284 --> 34:30.552
The problem is we can't
convince the court of anything.

34:30.587 --> 34:32.120
I'm not a lawyer yet,

34:32.156 --> 34:34.121
and I was hoping you
could do it, but then...

34:34.158 --> 34:35.524
It's okay.

34:35.559 --> 34:37.426
I've got just the person.

34:37.460 --> 34:40.695
[footsteps approaching]

34:41.860 --> 34:43.553
Harvey.

34:43.554 --> 34:44.719
Can I come in?

34:44.755 --> 34:47.755
Depends on why you're here.

34:47.791 --> 34:50.692
I'm here to apologize
for the way I acted last night.

34:50.728 --> 34:52.627
Is this 'cause Bobby
came to see you?

34:52.663 --> 34:54.896
No, it's because
Marcus got sick,

34:54.931 --> 34:57.532
and you took care of him, and
he couldn't even tell me that.

34:57.568 --> 34:59.434
- Harvey--
- I'm so angry.

34:59.470 --> 35:01.036
I don't want to be
angry anymore,

35:01.071 --> 35:02.771
but I don't know how to stop.

35:02.806 --> 35:04.473
Then let me say
how sorry I am

35:04.508 --> 35:06.742
for all the pain
that I have caused you.

35:06.777 --> 35:08.643
You don't need to tell me
how sorry you are.

35:08.679 --> 35:10.612
Yes, I do.

35:10.647 --> 35:13.915
Harvey, we both
may have played a part

35:13.951 --> 35:15.817
in the last 20 years,

35:15.853 --> 35:17.853
but I was an adult,

35:17.888 --> 35:20.756
and I put you
in that position.

35:21.143 --> 35:23.410
And not a day goes by

35:23.445 --> 35:26.480
that I don't understand
why you hate me.

35:26.515 --> 35:29.049
I was your mother.

35:29.084 --> 35:32.686
[voice breaking]
I was supposed to protect you...

35:32.721 --> 35:34.688
not scar you.

35:36.125 --> 35:37.624
Harvey...

35:37.659 --> 35:41.027
I am so sorry.

35:43.465 --> 35:46.633
[sighs]
I don't hate you, Mom.

35:48.403 --> 35:52.672
I hate what you did,
and I probably always will,

35:52.707 --> 35:54.941
but I don't hate you.

35:57.112 --> 35:59.212
I'll take that.

35:59.247 --> 36:03.249
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:03.618 --> 36:05.985
What is it?

36:06.020 --> 36:08.954
It's nothing.
It's...

36:08.990 --> 36:10.590
it's just, I had your
painting on my wall

36:10.625 --> 36:14.960
for the longest time,
and I just realized...

36:14.996 --> 36:17.062
how much I missed it.

36:19.100 --> 36:21.166
I love you, Harvey.

36:21.202 --> 36:24.169
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:24.205 --> 36:26.438
I love you, too, Mom.

36:26.474 --> 36:30.976
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:32.432 --> 36:34.659
Your Honor, my client is
a single mother

36:34.661 --> 36:35.760
with two small children.

36:35.796 --> 36:37.729
And my dog is
a Labrador retriever.

36:37.764 --> 36:39.497
But the only thing
that's relevant here

36:39.533 --> 36:41.900
is that his client hasn't paid
her rent in three months.

36:41.935 --> 36:44.436
And the reason she hasn't paid
it is because she's had no heat

36:44.471 --> 36:45.837
and a broken window
all winter,

36:45.872 --> 36:47.739
despite repeated requests
for repairs.

36:47.774 --> 36:49.541
There's absolutely
no documentation

36:49.576 --> 36:50.920
of any such request.
That's not true.

36:50.944 --> 36:52.110
My client called her landlord

36:52.145 --> 36:54.012
20 times over the course
of two months,

36:54.047 --> 36:55.680
as you can see
from her phone records.

36:55.716 --> 36:57.182
That's not proof
of anything.

36:57.217 --> 36:58.650
It's proof your client
spoke to mine

36:58.685 --> 37:00.129
for an average
of two minutes per call,

37:00.153 --> 37:02.487
and it wasn't to talk
about the weather.

37:02.522 --> 37:03.988
Your Honor,
Mr. Grady gave me

37:04.024 --> 37:05.890
a copy of this nonsense
20 minutes ago,

37:05.926 --> 37:08.359
and he specifically agreed
it wasn't relevant.

37:08.395 --> 37:09.728
That--that is a lie.

37:09.763 --> 37:11.696
Really?
Because I have a phone record

37:11.732 --> 37:14.466
of a two-minute call
that I made to you

37:14.501 --> 37:17.869
ten minutes ago.

37:17.904 --> 37:20.338
You may have called me,
but we didn't talk about that.

37:20.373 --> 37:22.373
That's right.
Just because I called you

37:22.409 --> 37:26.311
doesn't mean I can prove
what we talked about.

37:26.346 --> 37:28.213
Your Honor,
she called 20 times.

37:28.248 --> 37:29.981
Yeah, probably to say
why her rent was late,

37:30.016 --> 37:31.583
because she never paid it.

37:31.618 --> 37:32.917
But we won't know that

37:32.953 --> 37:34.330
because we don't have it
in writing,

37:34.354 --> 37:37.455
which is what
the court requires.

37:38.321 --> 37:40.254
Your Honor, I need...

37:40.289 --> 37:42.367
I'd like to request time
to confer with my supervisor.

37:42.391 --> 37:44.725
His supervisor?
He's a lawyer.

37:44.760 --> 37:46.004
- You have to help him.
- I can't.

37:46.028 --> 37:48.128
I just need a minute
to--to gather my thoughts.

37:48.164 --> 37:49.663
What is this,
preschool circle time?

37:49.699 --> 37:52.199
Your Honor, the woman
didn't pay her rent.

37:52.234 --> 37:53.434
The deadline is now.

37:53.469 --> 37:55.369
We are requesting
permission to evict

37:55.404 --> 37:57.805
if we don't have a check
by 10:00 a.m. tomorrow.

37:57.840 --> 38:01.308
- Your Honor, please.
- She's gonna lose her home.

38:01.344 --> 38:04.311
Time's up, counselor.
Permission granted.

38:04.347 --> 38:07.281
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

38:07.316 --> 38:10.651
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:15.589 --> 38:17.289
Harvey, what are you
doing here?

38:17.324 --> 38:18.824
When did you get back?

38:18.859 --> 38:21.226
Ten minutes ago.

38:21.262 --> 38:23.295
How'd it go?

38:23.330 --> 38:25.297
It went well.

38:27.101 --> 38:28.967
I'm glad.

38:31.138 --> 38:34.339
As a matter of fact,
I need your help with something.

38:34.375 --> 38:35.574
Anything.

38:35.609 --> 38:37.442
But there's something
you have to do first.

38:40.681 --> 38:42.214
- Mr. Ross.
- Miss Price.

38:42.249 --> 38:43.894
I wanted to talk to you.
Do you have a minute?

38:43.918 --> 38:45.384
Not really.

38:45.419 --> 38:48.287
They're coming tomorrow.
I've been packing, and--

38:48.322 --> 38:49.688
They're not coming.

38:54.862 --> 38:56.628
$3,600?

38:56.664 --> 38:58.775
Should be enough to cover your
rent for the last three months.

38:58.799 --> 39:00.632
- I don't understand.
- The clinic has a fund

39:00.668 --> 39:02.234
to help
with this kind of thing.

39:02.269 --> 39:03.936
We do it all the time.

39:03.971 --> 39:06.505
But this is from you.

39:06.540 --> 39:08.574
It's just quicker to do it
from my account--

39:08.609 --> 39:12.511
you know, red tape
and all that.

39:12.841 --> 39:14.652
- I don't know what to say.
- Say you'll take that

39:14.676 --> 39:16.710
to your landlord
first thing in the morning.

39:16.745 --> 39:19.145
And if they do anything
but give you a written receipt,

39:19.181 --> 39:21.715
you call me right away.

39:21.750 --> 39:23.783
I will. Thank you.

39:23.819 --> 39:25.819
[both chuckle]

39:31.378 --> 39:33.344
- You're back.
- I am.

39:33.380 --> 39:37.048
And I heard you took care
of my client.

39:37.084 --> 39:38.950
Thanks, Louis.

39:38.985 --> 39:42.053
You're welcome,
but we're partners,

39:42.089 --> 39:43.988
and they're all our clients.

39:44.024 --> 39:46.157
They are.

39:46.193 --> 39:48.560
Louis, I didn't mean it
when I said

39:48.595 --> 39:51.763
you weren't ready to be
managing partner.

39:51.798 --> 39:53.465
Yes, you did.

39:53.500 --> 39:55.967
Maybe I did,
but the truth is,

39:56.003 --> 39:59.037
I'm not ready either.

39:59.073 --> 40:03.241
What do you say we both act
as interim managing partners?

40:04.411 --> 40:06.044
I'd be honored.

40:08.716 --> 40:10.360
It seems to me,
the first order of business is,

40:10.384 --> 40:12.651
what are we gonna do about
the name of the firm?

40:14.421 --> 40:17.656
I don't know
about you, but...

40:17.691 --> 40:20.025
I think we should keep it
exactly the same.

40:20.060 --> 40:21.326
Me too.

40:21.362 --> 40:22.627
I mean, you never know

40:22.663 --> 40:25.464
when she's gonna want
to come back, right?

40:25.499 --> 40:29.368
No, Louis.
You never know.

40:29.403 --> 40:32.337
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

40:33.373 --> 40:38.309
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:38.344 --> 40:40.478
What are you two
still doing here?

40:40.513 --> 40:41.979
We've still got 12 hours.

40:42.014 --> 40:44.548
We're not going to stop trying
to keep Sofia in her apartment.

40:44.584 --> 40:45.950
Good for you.

40:45.985 --> 40:49.520
But you don't
have to do it tonight.

40:51.491 --> 40:54.492
Turns out she got
a little grace period.

40:54.527 --> 40:55.993
How did she get that?

40:56.028 --> 40:57.628
It's amazing
what you can do

40:57.663 --> 40:59.730
when you care
about your clients.

41:02.201 --> 41:04.268
Then I guess
first thing tomorrow,

41:04.303 --> 41:07.605
we should plan our next move.

41:07.640 --> 41:09.607
I guess we should.

